AGI - Improved time > with the arrival of the first weekend of May> but bad weather may have other cards to play. Fresh and unstable currents run on the central Mediterranean with still unstable weather conditions in Italy. In the next few hours there is still aquazzoni and temporal scattered >- we read in a note of the Italian Centre Metreo - especially on the internal zones of the Centre-Sud>. With the arrival of the first weekend of May, however, a general improvement is expected thanks to a small anti-cyclonic promontory in extension on the central-western Mediterranean. Dryer time and also rise temperatures with values in line or at least above averages. Latest updates of the Italian Weather Centre, which for the next week show the possibility of a new phase of bad weather. This is in fact that a depression could reach the Mediterranean and isolate itself as a cold drop at altitude, renew unstable weather conditions with thunderstorms for several days.
&nbsp;
OGGI AL NORD>.&nbsp; Stable time in the morning with cloudyness and lightening, local phenomena on the central-eastern Alps with snow over 1800-1900 meters. In the afternoon rains and storms in development on the Alps and Apennines with snow over 2000-2200 meters, dryer elsewhere. In the evening, the Alpine border to the plains. Improves in the night but with still many clouds.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
AL CENTRO>. In the morning rains on the Tyrrhenian sectors, dry variability elsewhere and serene skies on the Adriatic sectors. In the afternoon increasing instability with aquazzoni and temporal in development in the internal zones and in boundlessness on the Adriatic side. In the evening time in general improvement with exhaustion of phenomena but still some cloudy disorder.
&nbsp;
AL SUD AND ON ISOLE>. In the morning clouds scattered with local rains on Campania, serene or little cloudy elsewhere. In the afternoon aquazzoni and temporal in development in Appennino with treasury over the Adriatic regions. Time improving from the evening but with still cloudy disorders. Minimum temperatures in general decrease, maximum stable or in slight rise to the North West and Sardinia and in a slight decrease on the rest of Italy.
&nbsp;
